interfaces

Interface ITestRunner

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ExcelTestRunner

    public interface ITestRunner
    Primary interface model for executing ITestCase implementations This Interface will run Framework Keywords, Custom created Keywords, and Page Object methods
    Author:
    Mathew Carrigan

      • runCustomMethod

        default void runCustomMethod(java.lang.String objects,
                             java.util.List<java.lang.String> params)
        Runs a Page Object method. Currently ONLY parameterless page object methods are supported by Excel test runner
        Parameters:
        objects - String of the Keyword name provided in the Keyword column of an Excel Test Case. This string will be split by a '.' as it should be in the syntax of class.method format
        params - List of params from the params column of an Excel Test Case.

      • runCustomKeyword

        default void runCustomKeyword(java.lang.String keywordName,
                              java.util.List<ObjectDef> defs,
                              java.util.List<java.lang.String> params)
        Runs a Custom created Keyword that is NOT part of the Framework's provided keywords
        Parameters:
        keywordName - Name of the Keyword in the following Syntax: package.Class
        defs - List of ObjectDef objects- ObjectDefs are created by supplying a String name of the object in format of Class.Field and the Field should be either a By locator or a WebElement
        params - List of params to supply to the keyword

      • runKeyword

        default void runKeyword(java.lang.String keywordName,
                        java.util.List<ObjectDef> defs,
                        java.util.List<java.lang.String> params)
                 throws java.lang.InstantiationException,
                        java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        Runs a Framework provided Keyword
        Parameters:
        keywordName - Name of the Keyword to run
        defs - List of ObjectDef objects- ObjectDefs are created by supplying a String name of the object in format of Class.Field and the Field should be either a By locator or a WebElement
        params - List of Params to supply to the keyword
        Throws:
        java.lang.InstantiationException - If the provided Keyword name is not found
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - If the keyword does not properly implement the instantiateExternal method.

      • getObjectDefs

        default java.util.List<ObjectDef> getObjectDefs(ITestStep step)
                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Helper method that converts a List of Strings of PageObject fields and finds their actual Objects using reflection and converts them into ObjectDef instances The ObjectDef instance stores the actual Object and the Type of that object in order be able to determine if it is a By locator or a WebElement
        Parameters:
        step - ITestStep which contains a list of Objects as Strings
        Returns:
        List of ObjectDefs representing the actual objects
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if issues finding the object on the provided class or if there is an issue with access modifiers like private
